<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-04T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="1024" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1024">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.77/176</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Blanchard</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-04T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your November 20, noon. Your despatch April 30, No. 136, enclosure 1.
                            Again present matter of signature and delivery of bonds, to the end that
                            this be accomplished without further delay.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>